div1.p: In the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington.
In the Matter of the Application of Moy Share Park for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.
Filed in the United States District Court
In the Matter of the Appliction of Moy Share Park for a Writ of Habeas Corpus
To the Honorable Jeremiah Neterer, Judge of the District Court of the United States, for the Western District of Washington:

Now comes the respondent, Henry M. White, United States Commissioner of Immigration for the District of Washington, and produced the body of Moy Share Park in obedience to the command and direction of the writ of habeas corpus in the above entitled matter, being the person named in the petition for said writ.

For answer and return to said writ respondent avers that he detained in his custody the body of said Moy Share Park for deportation from the United States as an alien Chinese person, not entitled to admission under the laws of the United States, under and by virtue of an order of the Secretary of Commerce and Labor of the United States issued to him, and respondent, said order being in the words and figures following, to-wit:
"Department of Labor Bureau of Immigration Washington.
Acknowledging the receipt of your letter of the 12th ultimo, No. 37121/3-1, and confirming telegraphic advices furnished you today, you are informed that the
Assistant Secretary has dismissed the appeal of Moy Share Park and directed his deportation.
The exhibits forwarded with your letter are returned herewith.

Respondent attaches hereto the records, decisions, and exhibits, both on the hearing before him as commissioner of immigration and the hearing on appeal to the Secretary of Labor, which constitute a part of this return.
And now the respondent having fully answered, he prays that the said writ may be discharged.
Henry M. White, being first duly sworn, upon his oath deposes and says:
That he is the commissioner od immigration named in the foregoing return; that he has read the said return and knows the contents thereof, and that he beleives the same to be true.
Subscribed and sworn to before me this 23rd day of April,1920.
